But man, no one is telling her that Enemy Step is essential to Nero's play style. text:
Honestly, I got a bit fed up with bosses as Nero too. I feel like the expectation is to use the Arm-Grab as a counter to a lot of bosses and punish them, but there's no visual cues at all and looks like something you're supposed to know ahead of time, or constantly risk getting hit testing it out (and how are you supposed to know if you just messed the timing or if it can't be countered?). Luckily Gura started to catch onto Nero's exceed play, which I think is one of the most rewarding features when mastered.
Praying to see DMC sneak into next week's schedule

text:
Thanks for the stream sweet tato!!! I heard you talking bout tatos! I got triggered! Thanks for being sweet to us!! I was thinking about what you should do with your 3d model and I got 2 ideas. 

Firstly, a karaoke stream. You could do like Ame does and just use the tracking gear. That way you wouldn’t get sick and you could still shake that cute little tail! If I got to hear you sing and see your sweet Sharkie dance moves, I would die happy. 

The other is a 3d acclimation therapy endurance stream. So, I’ve read that if you take a break as soon as you feel the tiniest bit sick and then start again after the break, and keep doing that over and over it will help you to get over it. You could ask chat real sweet if we would help You, and of course chat will jump on board. We could have small zatusdans as the breaks. And if you take a break every time you start to feel bad You shouldn’t get sick.  And we can test if it really works and how well it increases your tolerance after. 

Furthermore, I love my shork! Have a good night and sorry i typed so much! I don’t blame you if you skip reading it either! Bless your noodle you sweet tato!
